article.headline: SE Louisiana 52, Stephen F. Austin 41
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Nate Lofton scored 14 points to lead Southeastern Louisiana past Stephen F. Austin 52-41 on Saturday. Jonathan Patton added 13 points and Ricky Woods had 11 for Southeastern Louisiana (19-7, 11-2 Southland Conference), which remained in first place with the victory. Southeastern Louisiana led the entire game and held Stephen F. Austin (11-12, 5-7) without a player in double-figure scoring. Leonard Brown led the Lumberjacks with eight points. The Lumberjacks have lost three straight.
